# Voice-Control System - Setup Guide

This project allows hands-free control of your system using voice commands via a Bluetooth-connected microphone. Features include opening apps, controlling volume, locking/unlocking system, and scanning Bluetooth devices.


## 📦 Requirements



Install all required libraries:
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
Note: Mac users may need to install pyaudio using brew install portaudio first.

▶️ How to Run
Connect your Bluetooth mic.

Open terminal and run:

bash
Copy
Edit
python voice_control.py
Speak commands like:

"open chrome"

"lock laptop"

"scan bluetooth"

"connect bluetooth device_name"

❌ To Stop
Say: "exit" or "stop" anytime.

Enjoy voice freedom 🗣💻

